# `select` inside a `parallel for` is now allowed, BUT the parfor body gates
# still fire inside its arms: a chunk cannot early-exit, so a `return` (or
# break/mut-capture) in a select arm must still be rejected. This locks the
# parity that the select-arm scan reuses the same gates as any other body --
# tychoc via pf_scan_stmt recursing into the arm, which hits S_RETURN.
fn main():
    a := channel(int, 8)
    send(a, 1)
    parallel for i in range(0, 1):
        select:
            recv(a, x):
                return
    print("unreachable\n")
